Sentencas: Symmetric-structure metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells (MS-SOFCs) are fabricated by infiltrating catalysts on both anode and cathode side.
Titulo: Development of High Power Density Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Various aspects of the infiltration process are optimized.
Titulo: Development of High Power Density Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Performance is found to be sensitive to precursor dilution, catalyst loading, and catalyst calcining temperature.
Titulo: Development of High Power Density Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: For an optimized cell with lanthanum strontium manganite (LSM) as cathode and Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-delta mixed with Ni (SDCN) as anode, peak power densities of 0.44, 1.1, and 1.9 Wcm(-2) are achieved at 600, 700, and 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Development of High Power Density Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: A fully symmetric MS-SOFC with SDCN as both the anode and cathode sides achieves moderate peak power densities of 0.12, 0.37, and 0.76Wcm(-2) at 600, 700, and 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Development of High Power Density Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: A solvent-based infiltration technique is also explored and found to be more effective than capillary forces alone but not as effective as vacuum infiltration.
Titulo: Development of High Power Density Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
